-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -2.505ex; width:32.668ex; height:6.009ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle A\=
;=3D\;2\int _{-r}^{r}{\sqrt {r^{2}-x^{2}}}\,dx\;=3D\;\pi r^{2}.}"></span></=
dd></dl>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading4"><h4 id=3D"Ellipses">Ellipses</h4><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DArea&amp;action=3Ded=
it&amp;section=3D18" title=3D"Edit section: Ellipses"><span>edit</span></a>=
<span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<link rel=3D"mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href=3D"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r=
1320445320"><div role=3D"note" class=3D"hatnote navigation-not-searchable">=
Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ellipse#Area" title=
=3D"Ellipse">Ellipse =C2=A7&nbsp;Area</a></div>
<p>The formula for the area enclosed by an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Ellipse" title=3D"Ellipse">ellipse</a> is related to the formula o=
f a circle; for an ellipse with <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Se=
mi-major_axis" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Semi-major axis">semi-major</=
a> and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Semi-minor_axis" class=3D"m=
w-redirect" title=3D"Semi-minor axis">semi-minor</a> axes <span class=3D"te=
xhtml"><i>x</i></span> and <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>y</i></span> the form=
ula is:<sup id=3D"cite_ref-AF_2-6" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://e=
n.wikipedia.org/wiki/Area#cite_note-AF-2"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</s=
pan>2<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e A=3D\pi xy.}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>A</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <mi>=CF=80<!-- =CF=80 --></mi>
        <mi>x</mi>
        <mi>y</mi>
        <mo>.</mo>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle A=3D\pi xy.}<=
/annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/a81da558d3d525f9ff7688980d2788087713390f" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.671ex; width:9.306ex; height:2.509ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle A=
