-image-display mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertica=
l-align: -0.838ex; width:46.347ex; height:3.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle f=
(x)-g(x)=3Dax^{2}+bx+c=3Da(x-\alpha )(x-\beta )}"></span>
where <i>f</i>(<i>x</i>) is the quadratic upper bound and <i>g</i>(<i>x</i>=
) is the quadratic lower bound.=20
By the area integral formulas above and <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org=
/wiki/Vieta%27s_formulas" title=3D"Vieta's formulas">Vieta's formula</a>, w=
